## Last-Resort-Exceptions

**Rebuttal 1:** Cannot absorb this branch into target because the target's CI configuration cannot absorb the custom hooks used here. However, archival-not-deletion is insufficient because the residual gap of the hook logic must remain recoverable. We have, nonetheless, verified that the underlying data flows are unaffected.

**Rebuttal 2:** Will not absorb this module: target lacks the runtime dependency. The outstanding gap is the dependency lockfile. Trade-off: re-deriving the lockfile on restore is acceptable. Archival alone is not enough — restore must remain verifiable.

**Rebuttal 3:** Cannot absorb due to license incompatibility. Rebutted: this is why we archive rather than delete. The residual gap is the upstream license header; remains unresolved until upstream relicenses.

## Restore-Command

```bash
mv .archive/sample-repo .
# OR
git clone https://example.com/sample-repo
sha256: a1b2c3d4e5f6...
```

bin/repo-delete-gate.sh was invoked before archival. The deletion gate has already 404'd the remote.